race.comment: CHERYL'S SHOUT (4) missed by 1.8L two back at Albany before going under narrowly when setting the tempo at York last time out. Slightly tougher here, but she's shown she's capable of mixing it in tougher grades recently. Blinkers go back on and she can go one better this time around. MAGICASH (7) was 2.2L away at Belmont first-up where she jumped the fave and now drops right back in grade today. The wide draw is a query, but she does have early speed and if she can improve on the fresh run, she'll be very hard to beat. ZAC LUVS TO FLY (2) is building nicely this time in work and loves this track and trip. He can roll forward from the gate and he'll be very hard to run down. FAVOURITE SONGS (9) can improve on the fresh effort at Northam as she drops back in class. WEAPONS HOT (1) is better than he showed last time out and can bounce back.
